data.title: Spirited Away
data.synopsis: In this animated feature by noted Japanese director Hayao Miyazaki, 10-year-old Chihiro and her parents stumble upon a seemingly abandoned amusement park. After her mother and father are turned into giant pigs, Chihiro meets the mysterious Haku, who explains that the park is a resort for supernatural beings who need a break from their time spent in the earthly realm, and that she must work there to free herself and her parents.

data.title: Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood
data.synopsis: Brothers Edward and Alphonse Elric search for the Philosopher's Stone, hoping to restore their bodies, which were lost when they attempted an alchemy ritual to bring their deceased mother back to life.

data.title: Your Name
data.synopsis: A teenage boy and girl embark on a quest to meet each other for the first time after they magically swap bodies and discover that they have a connection that has them searching for answers.

data.title: Re:ZERO -Starting Life in Another World-
data.synopsis: Natsuki Subaru, an ordinary high school student, is on his way home from the convenience store when he finds himself transported to another world. As he's lost and confused in a new world where he doesn't even know left from right, the only person to reach out to him was a beautiful girl with silver hair.

data.title: March Comes in Like a Lion
data.synopsis: This is a story about Rei, a lone player in the competitive world of professional shogi board gaming. The series follows Rei’s growth as a player and as a person while exploring themes of depression, anxiety, and adoption.

data.title: Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood
data.synopsis: Two brothers search for a Philosopher's Stone after an attempt to revive their deceased mother goes awry and leaves them in damaged physical forms.

data.title: Attack on Titan
data.synopsis: After his hometown is destroyed and his mother is killed, young Eren Yeager vows to cleanse the earth of the giant humanoid Titans that have brought humanity to the brink of extinction.

data.title: Re:Zero − Starting Life in Another World
data.synopsis: Subaru Natsuki is a NEET who is suddenly summoned to a fantasy world. He soon discovers he has the ability to rewind death, akin to a time travel of sorts.

data.title: Sword Art Online
data.synopsis: In the year 2022, thousands of people get trapped in a new virtual MMORPG and the lone wolf player, Kirito, works to escape.

data.title: No Game No Life
data.synopsis: Siblings Sora and Shiro are transported to a world where life is a series of games and humanity is in jeopardy of extinction.

data.title: Fruits Basket: The Final
data.synopsis: Tohru Honda continues her journey with the Soma family, learning more about their cursed fate, while they all confront their past and prepare for a future where they can be their true self.

data.title: Clannad: After Story
data.synopsis: Following the events of the first season, Tomoya Okazaki and Nagisa Furukawa graduate from high school and face the challenges of adulthood, family matters, and expanding their own little family.

data.title: Your Lie in April
data.synopsis: Kousei Arima, a piano prodigy loses his ability to hear the sound of piano after his mother's death. His monotone life begins to gain color when he meets a violinist, Kaori Miyazono, who stirs up his world and sets him on a journey to face music again.

data.title: March Comes in Like a Lion
data.synopsis: Rei Kiriyama is a 17-year-old shogi player who lives alone. His relationship with his foster family is strained, and he has difficulty interacting with his peers. As he struggles with his professional career and personal life, Rei slowly learns how to interact with others and understand his own complex emotions.

data.title: Anohana: The Flower We Saw That Day
data.synopsis: A group of childhood friends grows apart after the death of one of them, Menma. Years later, her ghost appears and asks them to grant her a wish she never got to fulfill, thus, they reunite to help her move on and to reconcile with their own grief and regrets.
